The paper focuses on developing a framework for robots to navigate safely and efficiently using local 3D information, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses incorporating pose uncertainty in motion planning, which involves machine learning (cs.CV, cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed framework, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
